The paper focuses on autonomous navigation of a robot in an unknown environment, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed map representation and online training algorithm involve machine learning techniques, specifically kernel perceptron classifiers, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions collision checking using piecewise-linear and piecewise-polynomial trajectories, which could involve computer vision techniques for detecting obstacles (cs.CV). The use of support vectors and sparse representations in the proposed algorithm suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with control and decision-making for the robot's navigation, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
